          },
          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Photodisintegration of He-4."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "H.G.Clerc",
                "R.J.Stewart",
                "R.C.Morrison"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,PL,18,316,1965",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,PL,18,316,1965",
                    "doi": "10.1016/0031-9163(65)90353-7",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "PL",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "18",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "316"
                      },
                      "date": 1965
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "1USAYAL"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAYAL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "QMPH",
                  "KINDT"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The Bremsstrahlung source of incident",
                " gamma-quanta. But for He-4(gamma,p)H-3 reaction one",
                " has a breakup into two particles which do not have",
                " excited states. The measured angle and energy of",
                " only one of the emitted particles therefore",
                " determine the energy of the gamma-quantum that",
                " produced the reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGFR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Quadrupole triplet."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Semiconductor detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The He-4 gas target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For experimental reasons, tritons could be detected",
                " only in the higher gamma ray energy region. The low",
                " energy region had to be studied by measuring protons,",
                " although protons from the three-body (d,p,n) and",
                " four-body (p,p,n,n) breakup reactions interfere. The",
                " contribution of these reactions which have higher",
                " thresholds (26 and 28 MeV, respectively) was however,",
                " minimized by working at a low maximum Bremsstrahlung",
                " energy of 40 MeV. By alternating the He-4 target with",
                " a H-2 target, the He-4 cross section was obtained",
                " relative to that of the deuteron photodisintegration.",
                " To convert to an absolute cross section, a",
                " theoretical cross section for the photodisintegration",
                " of deuteron as calculated by Donnachie and O'Donnell",
                " was used (solution with 6% d-state and retardation",
                " included). In analyzing of multipolarity of cross",
                " section it was assumed that coefficient 'beta' which",
                " determine the E2 term varies from 0.2 at Eg = 27 MeV",
                " to 0.7 at Eg = 52 MeV. Therefore the error in the",
                " cross section arising from the inaccurately known",
                " value of 'beta' does not exceed about 10%, even for",
                " the highest energies in this experiment."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REL-REF": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "R",
                "subentry_number": null,
                "author": "A.Donnachie+",
                "reference": {
                  "code": "J,NP,53,128,1964",
